3/15/2017

In this lesson, we will look at how land use change affects downstream water quality.

Data Prep

Read in key libraries

Read in raw data

Data comes from several sources

  • Q data comes from USGS for stations:
    • 09046600, Blue River above Dillon Reservoir
    • 09047500, Snake River near Montezuma
  • Water Quality is downloaded from STORET database from several sources:
    • RiverWatch Network
    • Colorado Department of Publich Health and Environment
  • Spatial data comes from NHD Plus

Manipulate and cast data to extract yearly means of concentration data for key constituents.

sub.full <- dat.full %>%
  filter(Characteristic.Name %in% key.params) %>%
  mutate(Units=ifelse(grepl('mg/l',Units),'mg/l',Units)) %>%
  mutate(Units=ifelse(grepl('ug/l',Units),'ug/l',Units)) %>%
  mutate(Result.Value.as.Number=ifelse(Units=='mg/l',Result.Value.as.Number*1000,Result.Value.as.Number)) %>%
  mutate(Units=gsub('mg/l','ug/l',Units)) %>%
  mutate(Name= ifelse(grepl('Inorganic',Characteristic.Name),'Nitrogen.N',Characteristic.Name)) %>%
  mutate(Units=ifelse(grepl('None',Units),'None',Units))



chem.cast <- dcast(sub.full,Activity.Start+Station.ID ~ Name, value.var='Result.Value.as.Number',mean)

chem.cast$date <- ymd_hms(chem.cast$Activity.Start) 

chem.melt <- melt(chem.cast,id.vars=c('date','Station.ID'),measure.vars=key.params)

ggplot(chem.melt, aes(x=date,y=value,color=Station.ID)) + geom_point(show.legend = F) + facet_wrap(~variable,scales='free')
## Warning: Removed 854 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Read in Q data

q <- read.delim('data/BlueRiverQ.txt',stringsAsFactors = F,comment.char='#')
names(q) <- c('agency','site','datetime','Q','quality')
q <- q[-1,]


chem.melt$day <- date(chem.melt$date)
head(chem.melt)
##                  date Station.ID variable value        day
## 1 1997-05-20 12:09:00      12337 Aluminum    NA 1997-05-20

## 5 2000-10-18 11:35:00      12336 Aluminum    NA 2000-10-18

q$Q <- as.numeric(q$Q) %>% stats::filter(.,rep(1/5,5)) %>% as.numeric(.)
q$lps <- q$Q*28.3168 #Convert Q to lps
q$day <- ymd(q$datetime)

q.chem <- left_join(q,chem.melt,by='day') %>% filter(!is.na(value)) %>%
  mutate(qvalue=value/lps)


g2 <- ggplot(q.chem, aes(x=lps,y=value,color=Station.ID)) + geom_point(show.legend=F) + facet_wrap(~variable,scales='free') + 
  scale_x_log10()
